defs.name: bounded_k_partition_ratio
defs.value: fn bounded_k_partition_ratio(usize, usize, usize, usize) -> f64

attributes.value: / If (r, k, n) denotes the number of k-partitions of n such that all elements in the partition are <= r
/ this function computes an approximation of (r, k-1, n-m) / (r, k, n); so this computes the probability
/ that one element of the partition has the value of m.
/ Note that because of the approximations the a distribution generated using this function may not be normalized
/ We have to renormalize the distribution because we work with approximations.

defs.docs:
If (r, k, n) denotes the number of k-partitions of n such that all elements in the partition are <= r
 this function computes an approximation of (r, k-1, n-m) - which acts as a stand-in for the probability
 that one element of the partition has the value of m that is given by (r, k-1, n-m) / (r, k, n).
